Description: Fragment of rim, neck and shoulder, with complete twin-reed handle, of East Greek pottery trefoil oenochoe; very worn glaze traces, though not readily distinguished from surface dirt. Ginger-buff very micaceous clay.
Curator's comments: Almost certainly from same, worn, jug as 1886,0401.915.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.583)
